{"TopicId":154667,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Set custom target orbit","CreatedByName":"Piratdu52","CreatedById":161333,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-07T23:38:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Piratdu52","CreatedById":161333,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-07T23:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had recently a bug with a mod\u00A0mission, i don\u0027t had the final required orbit of my sat showed in the map screen. Pretty annoying. But this give me an an idea. Why not a mod to be able able to set a custom target orbit \u00A0around an object ? It\u0027s can be useful for debug an place network relay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-07T23:38:57Z\u0022 title=\u002201/07/2017 11:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Piratdu52\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheRagingIrishman","CreatedById":165004,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T00:50:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/34785-12-hyperedit-v153-sep-14-2016-cheat-teleporter-orbitplanet-editor-more/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Piratdu52","CreatedById":161333,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-08T09:43:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not what i asked. The goal is to add a target orbit in map view not to teleport your vessel or a planet around an other object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-08T12:15:19Z\u0022 title=\u002201/08/2017 12:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Piratdu52\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T09:38:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo basically, you want to be able to use, as a player, the system that contracts use to put up those colored destination orbit lines for satellite contracts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T20:37:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222914373\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483868627\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Piratdu52\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 08/01/2017 at 7:43 AM, Piratdu52 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not what i asked. The goal is to add a target orbit in map view not to teleport your vessel or a planet around an other object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhowever you may teleport a different vessel (like a single probecore) so you can target it to use as guidance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Piratdu52","CreatedById":161333,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-09T23:36:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222915340\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483954721\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Streetwind\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Streetwind said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo basically, you want to be able to use, as a player, the system that contracts use to put up those colored destination orbit lines for satellite contracts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it\u0027s that.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222916041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221483994272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spricigo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Spricigo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhowever you may teleport a different vessel (like a single probecore) so you can target it to use as guidance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan be a good idea. If a mod like this is done, why not set one or more flag in the contract or custom orbit. This can be very useful if you try to place 3 satellite at equidistance on the same orbit \u00A0for relay purpose. Like this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022oDkgqgU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/oDkgqgU.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-09T23:38:49Z\u0022 title=\u002201/09/2017 11:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Piratdu52\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}